1. What is a Program?
A program is a set of instructions given to a computer to perform a specific task.
Examples
ATM Machine
Calculator
Mobile Apps
Online Banking

2. What is Python?
Python is a high-level, interpreted, general-purpose programming language developed by Guido van Rossum.
Python is simple to read, write, and learn.

3. History of Python
Developed by Guido van Rossum
First released in 1991
Named after Monty Python's Flying Circus
Open-source programming language.

4. Features of Python
High-level language
Easy to learn
Easy to read
Interpreted language
Platform independent
Open source
Supports Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)
Large standard library

5. Interpreter vs Compiler
Interpreter
Executes program line by line.
Stops immediately if an error occurs.
Python uses an interpreter.
Compiler
Translates the entire program before execution.
Reports errors after compilation.

