8. String
A string is a sequence of characters enclosed in single (' ') or double (" ") quotes.
Examples:
"Python"
"Data Science"
"Hello World"

9. Variables
A variable is a named memory location used to store data.
Example:
name = "Anju"
print(name)
Another example:
age = 20
age = 21
Variables can change during program execution.

